@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "SafeKraker" where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  You play by clicking on the arrows which will increase or decrease
the numbers in their respective columns (an arrow pointing up will
increase the number and the arrow pointing down will decrease it).
If you click an 'up' arrow and its corresponding number is at 7, it
will 'wrap' to 1, and vice-versa for a 'down' arrow.

  You can also click on the '+' or '-' symbols located at the left,
these increase or decrease ALL 3 numbers simultaneously.

  Note that there will never be a combination that uses ALL the same
numbers (like 111, 222, etc.), so you don't have to worry about
these combinations (also, it would be too easy!).

  The game counts every 'move', that is, every time you click on an
arrow, '+' or '-' symbol. So try to find the secret code in the least
amount of moves possible...

  SafeKraker features two types of game: 

 -The 'Easy' game, where you change the numbers in each column, when
  you find one of the right numbers, it's corresponding padlock will
  open.

 -The 'Normal' game, where you have to find ALL THREE numbers in
  order to open all the padlocks. You have around 336 possible
  combinations to try!

  Have fun!

